Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveOn Tuesday, tens of thousands of Japanese people flooded the streets of Central Tokyo to bid Shinzo Abe, the slain former prime minister, farewell.
On Friday, Abe was shot while attending a political event.
After Abe’s funeral in Chiyoda Ward, Tokyo, the motor hearse carrying his remains passed in front of the prime minister’s office before continuing to a crematory with his wife, Akie.
 
